.TH "sigmadsp_attach" 9 "sigmadsp_attach" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sigmadsp_attach \- Attach a sigmadsp instance to a ASoC component
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sigmadsp_attach
.BI "(struct sigmadsp *sigmadsp "  ","
.BI "struct snd_soc_component *component "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sigmadsp" 12
The sigmadsp instance to attach
.IP "component" 12
The component to attach to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Typically called in the components probe callback.

Note, once this function has been called the firmware must not be released
until after the ALSA snd_card that the component belongs to has been
disconnected, even if \fBsigmadsp_attach\fP returns an error.
